@ossified:
  G6-OSS-01 KOBEST_INLINE_N_20_MIN baseline benchmark before HF loader wire
  G6-OSS-02 MC_LEADING_DIGIT_RUBRIC — HAE-RAE/MMLU-Ko grade by first 1..5 in first 20 bytes (fallback "" = wrong). Keeps grading deterministic across temp=0 runs and avoids contains() false positives on long replies with multiple digits.
  G6-OSS-03 PROMPT_FORMAT_DETERMINISTIC — "{problem_text}\n선택지:\n1) {c1}\n2) {c2}\n...\n답:" identical across HAE-RAE + MMLU-Ko. Single source of prompt shape (hr_prompt4 fn) means future suites (CLIcK, KorNLI, etc.) can reuse.
  G6-OSS-04 TOTAL_INLINE_CORPUS_CAP_60 — KoBEST 20 + HAE-RAE 20 + MMLU-Ko 20 = 60. Any future inline suite must replace items, not extend, to avoid hexa string-concat PERF warnings (kr_gen_sentinel / phi_correlation precedents at n=16).

@gap_1 HF loader still blocked — inline n=20 is smoke-grade, not production parity with ~6k HAE-RAE / ~35k KMMLU
